Soulswitch	TYPE:Arcane	CLASSES:Bard,Cleric,Druid,Inquisitor,Magus,Shaman,Sorcerer,Wizard,Witch=5	SCHOOL:Necromancy	COMPS:V, S, F (two brass collars worth 50 gp each)	CASTTIME:1 standard action	RANGE:Touch	TARGETAREA:You and your familiar	DURATION:(10*CASTERLEVEL) minutes	SOURCEPAGE:p.23		SAVEINFO:Will negates (harmless)	SPELLRES:Yes (harmless)	DESC:.|!PRERULE:1,DisplayFullSpell	DESC:You may only cast this spell if you currently have a familiar. You place your soul into the body of your familiar, and your familiar's soul is placed in your body. This functions as if you possessed your familiar using magic jar; your familiar simultaneously possesses your body in the same manner. You can't freely transfer your soul between your body and your familiar'sâ€”if you choose to return to your body as a standard action, the spell ends. If either body is killed, both spirits return to their original bodies, the spell ends, and the original owner of the slain body dies.|PRERULE:1,DisplayFullSpell
Transfer Familiar	TYPE:Arcane	CLASSES:Sorcerer,Wizard,Witch=6	SCHOOL:Evocation	COMPS:V, S	CASTTIME:1 standard action	RANGE:Touch	TARGETAREA:Your familiar and one willing creature	DURATION:(CASTERLEVEL) day	SOURCEPAGE:p.23		SAVEINFO:None	SPELLRES:No	DESC:.|!PRERULE:1,DisplayFullSpell	DESC:You temporarily grant control of your familiar to another willing creature. You, your familiar, and the target creature must all be touching each other when you cast this spell. The target gains all the benefits and abilities normally associated with having a familiar, including the ability to share spells, speak with the familiar, and so on. You lose all of these benefits for the duration of the spell. If the target already has a familiar, the spell fails.|PRERULE:1,DisplayFullSpell



